                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/12503: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Hungary</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Pell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Budapest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-27T10:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 27, 1941—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 27—7:37 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>391. Hungary this morning declared that because of Russian air raids on Kassa and
                    attempt on Budapest yesterday Hungary is now in a state of war with Soviet
                    Russia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Pell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
